Section : Prepare (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Please download the latest SettingsCarePA tool before start testing;
Noteï¼šSettingsCarePA tool doesn‘t support on ARM platform.

Before testing, please confirm with the project SPM which functions your machine supports. and put the result in column D of the attachment .
For some functions, please confirm the default status and put the result in column E of the attachment

During the execution of the test case, please complete the results in the attached "SettingCarePA tool Scan report". If there is a "Fail" in the Result column, please key issue
Note: Please do not fill in or change all NA items grayed out in the attachment

How to use  SettingsCarePA tool?

Open the downloaded tool SettingsCarePA-Plugins. There are folders for IdeaNotebookTool, MultimediaTool, OLEDSpirit, SuperResolutionTools, UEFICard, ZeroTouchSMATool, ECMTool etc.

Run IdeaGuiTool.exe in IdeaNotebookTool. Power and input related functions can be checked

Run MultimediaGUI.exe in MultimediaTool. Dolby,Microphone and Camera related functions can be checked

Run SpiritCard.exe in OLEDSpirit. OLED related functions can be checked

Run SuperResolutionTool.exe in SuperResolutionTools. SR related functions can be checked

Run ECMTools.exe in ECMTool. Eye Care mode related functions can be checked
 
Section : Interface scan (90) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Use the tool to check whether the following functional interfaces are supported, and fill the results in column F of the attachment

1.Smart Battery 1.0ï¼š

Launch IdeaGuiTool.exe-Power-Smart Battery.Check the status of "Support temporary mode"

If the result is True, please fill in "Y" in column F of smart battery1.0;
If the result is false, please fill in "N" in column F of the attachment smart battery1.0

2.Smart Battery 2.0:

Noteï¼šThis part only needs to test EN OS, not CN OS

Launch IdeaGuiTool.exe-Power-Smart Battery.Check the status of "Support Smart battery2.0"

If the result is True, please fill in "Y" in column F of smart battery2.0;
If the result is false, please fill in "N" in column F of the attachment smart battery2.0

3.Smart Battery 3.0:

Launch IdeaGuiTool.exe-Power-Smart Battery.Check the status of "Support battery night charge"

If the result is True, please fill in "Y" in column F of Support battery night charge;
If the result is false, please fill in "N" in column F of the attachment Support battery night charge

4.Conservation mode

Launch IdeaGuiTool.exe-Power-Conservation Mode.Check the status of "Support Conservation mode"

If the result is True, please fill in "Y" in column F of Conservation mode;
 If the result is false, please fill in "N" in column F of the attachment Conservation mode

Please check whether the value of "Charge threshold" is correct

Fill the results of "Charge threshold" in column F of "Charge threshold"

5.Rapid Charge

Launch IdeaGuiTool.exe-Power-Rapid Charge.Check the status of "Support Rapid Charge"

9.Eye Care mode

Noteï¼šThis part only needs to test EN OS, not CN OS

Launch ECMTools.exe-ECM and check the status of ThinkOrGamingï¼š
If the status of ThinkOrGaming is No, please test steps 9.1-9.3 below;


If the status of ThinkOrGaming is Yes,please test steps 9.4 below.

Launch ECMTools.exe- ECM and Check the  status of "Platform"ï¼š

9.1 When "Platform" is detected as "Intel Old Platform":
Check the status of ECMTools.exe-Intel Platform-Intel Old Platform:

If the status of "Interface Avaiable", "In AllowList" and "Win11" are all Yes in Intel Old Platformï¼š
Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Otherwise:
Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;

9.2 When "Platform" is detected as "Intel New  Platform", check the status of ECMTools.exe-Intel Platform-Intel ADL+ Platform

If the status of "Interface Avaiable" is  Yes in Intel ADL+ Platformï¼š
Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Otherwise:
Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;

9.3 When "Platform" is detected as "AMD Platform", check the status of ECMTools.exe-Intel Platform-AMD Platform

If the status of "Interface Avaiable" and "Driver Version"  are all  Yes in AMD Platformï¼š
Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Otherwise:
Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;

9.4 When the status of "ThinkOrGaming" is "Yes"

Please fill in "Y" in column F of Eye Care mode1.0 in the attachment;
Please fill in "N" in column F of Eye Care mode2.0 in the attachment;

10.Keyboard Backlight

Noteï¼š1.This part not support RGB lighting keyboard. (For example:Gaming project support RGB lighting keyboard ), please skip itï¼›

 If the result is false, please fill in "N" in column F of the attachment  Keyboard backlight

If the result of "Supported Backlight levels" is "Auto, Low, High, Off", please fill "4" in column F of the attachment "backlight levels";
If the result of "Supported Backlight levels" is " Low, High, Off", please fill "3" in column F of the attachment "backlight levels";
If the result of "Supported Backlight levels" is "On, Off", please fill "2" in column F of the attachment "backlight levels";


If not support Keyboard backlight: please fill in "N"
